The paper deals with the problem of calibrating a lidar to a sensor capable of providing egomotion information, which is a common problem in robotics and autonomous systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves point cloud reconstruction, which is a common problem in computer vision, hence cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely. The paper uses entropy-based techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning and information theory, hence cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possibility. The paper also involves camera calibration, which is a common problem in computer vision and robotics, hence cs.CVPR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also likely. Finally, the paper involves the use of simulations and data collected from a hand-held sensor rig, which involves data analysis and processing, hence cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possibility.
